- **Modules:** 5 plug-in boards

## Notes & sourcing

- All resistors are ¼ W, 1% metal-film, axial THT. Buy quantities rounded to common pack sizes — passives are cheap, keep spares.
- 10 µF electrolytics sit on 3V3 / 5V rails; ≥16 V rated works, 25 V gives margin. Keep the D5.0 mm body / 2.5 mm lead pitch to fit the footprint.
- Q1, U1, D1 are the only non-module semiconductors. **D1 (SMBJ12A TVS) is optional** — the board is functional without it; leave the SMB pad empty if you can't get one.
- ⚠ **Before trusting the board at full current:** replace **J1 / J2 / J3** (2.54 mm headers rated ~3 A) with XT60 / 5.08 mm screw terminals, and put **F1** (15 A) on an inline blade-fuse holder in the harness — not the PCB pin header.
- **XL4016 buck modules:** set output voltage with a multimeter **before** wiring to the board — 6.0 V for the servo rail, 5.0 V for the 5 V rail.
- **Encoders run on +3V3 ONLY** — 5 V on an ESP32 GPIO permanently damages it.
